val sun = sc.textFile("hdfs:///sun/sun")
val sunriseset = sun.map(s => s.split(","))
                    .map(s => (s(0),
                               s(1),
                               s(3))
                        )
                    .filter(_._1 > "2017-04-01")
                    .collect

def get_sunriseset_time(day: String) = {
    val e = sunriseset.filter(_._1 == day)(0)
    Map("rise" -> e._2, "set" -> e._3)
}

val cas_nt = sc.textFile("hdfs:///cas_nt/cas_nt")
                .map(s => s.split(","))
                .map(s => (s(0), //datetime
                            s(14), //photometric (2)
                            s(34), s(38), s(57) //cct, cri, swr (3,4,5)
                ))
                .toDF("datetime","lux",
                    "cct","cri","swr")

val cas_uv = sc.textFile("hdfs:///cas_uv/cas_uv")
                .map(s => s.split(","))
                .map(s => (s(0), //datetime
                            s(2), s(3), s(4), //CAS_UVB, CAS_UVA, CAS_VitDUV (2,3,4)
                            s(5), s(6), s(7), s(8) //CAS_EryUV, CAS_EryUVB, CAS_EryUVA, CAS_EryUVI (5,6,7,8)
                            ))
                .toDF("datetime", "UVB", "UVA", "DUV", "EUV", "EUVB", "EUVA", "UVI")

cas_nt.write.mode("overwrite").parquet("hdfs:///ds/nt_tmp.parquet")
cas_uv.write.mode("overwrite").parquet("hdfs:///ds/uv_tmp.parquet")

%pyspark
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import seaborn as sns
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from pyspark.sql.types import FloatType

wtob = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///ds/wtob.parquet')
nt = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///ds/nt_tmp.parquet')
uv = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///ds/uv_tmp.parquet')
wtntuv = wtob.join(nt, 'datetime')\
             .join(uv, 'datetime')

df = wtntuv

def floatize(s):
    try:
        ret = float(s)
    except ValueError:
        ret = -0.1
    return ret

udf_toFloat = udf(floatize, FloatType())

for col in df.columns:
    if col == 'datetime':
        continue
    df = df.withColumn(col + '_', udf_toFloat(df[col]))\
           .drop(col)

%pyspark
from pyspark.sql.types import StringType
from pyspark.sql.types import IntegerType

udf_dt2date = udf(lambda dt: dt.split(' ')[0], StringType())
udf_dt2hour = udf(lambda dt: int(dt.split(' ')[1].split(':')[0]), IntegerType())

df = df.withColumn('date', udf_dt2date(df['datetime']))\
       .withColumn('hour', udf_dt2hour(df['datetime']))

df.createOrReplaceTempView('wtntuv_1')

%sql
select 
    date,
    hour,
    uvindex_,
    UVI_
from wtntuv_1
